# Subjects

**Filters**

| **Name**      | **Type** | **Permitted values**          | **Description**                                            |
| ------------- | -------- | ----------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| ids | String | Integers | Return results tied to ids |
| types          | String   | radical, kanji, vocabulary    | Return subjects of the specified types                      |
| slugs         | String   | String                        | Return subjects of the specified slug                      |
| levels        | String   | Integers between 1 and 60     | Return subjects at the specified levels                    |
| hidden | Boolean | true, false | Return subjects which are or are not hidden from the user-facing application |
| updated_after | String   | ISO8601 timestamp in the past | Return results which have been updated after the timestamp |

## GET `/subjects/:id`

The structure depends on the subject type. Subject types are: radical, kanji, or vocabulary.

**Radical**

    {
      id: :integer,
      object: :string,
      url: :string,
      data_updated_at: :date,
      data: {
        level: :integer,
        created_at: :date,
        characters: :string_or_null,
        character_images: :array_of_objects,
        meanings: :array_of_objects,
        document_url: :string,
        hidden_at: :date_or_null
      }
    }

